# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Git LFS tracking rules — provided but DELIBERATELY LEFT COMMENTED OUT.
#
# None of the files in this repo currently need LFS — price_model.pkl (the
# largest artifact) is ~8.9 MB, and the whole repo is ~11 MB, well under
# GitHub's 50 MiB "you'll get a warning" threshold, let alone the 100 MiB hard
# block (see README.md "Repository size" section for the reasoning and sources).
#
# The rules below are kept COMMENTED so that plain `git add` / `git commit`
# stores these files as normal git blobs (which is exactly what you want at
# this size). If a future retrain with deeper trees / more estimators, or a
# bigger dataset, pushes any artifact toward GitHub's 100 MiB limit, simply
# UNCOMMENT the matching line(s) below, then:
#
#     git lfs install                       # one-time per machine
#     git add .gitattributes <the big file>
#     git commit -m "Track large files with Git LFS"
#
# (Context: these same forests once hit ~187 MB combined early in development,
# before depth-bounding — so the rules are pre-written for exactly that case.)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# *.pkl    filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
# *.csv    filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
# *.csv.gz filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
